<glossary>
<definition id="fs-id1167830838184">
<term>cost function</term>
<meaning id="fs-id1167834064000">The cost function is the cost to manufacture each unit times <m:math><m:mi>x</m:mi></m:math>, the number of units manufactured, plus the fixed costs; <emphasis effect="italics">C</emphasis>(<emphasis effect="italics">x</emphasis>) = (cost per unit)<emphasis effect="italics">x</emphasis> + fixed costs.</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-id1167834063600">
<term>revenue</term>
<meaning id="fs-id1167835337330">The revenue is the selling price of each unit times <emphasis effect="italics">x</emphasis>, the number of units sold; <emphasis effect="italics">R(x</emphasis>) = (selling price per unit)<emphasis effect="italics">x</emphasis>.</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-id1167834501281">
<term>break-even point</term>
<meaning id="fs-id1167826819275">The point at which the revenue equals the costs is the break-even point; <m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>C</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>)</m:mo></m:mrow><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mi>R</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>)</m:mo></m:mrow><m:mo>.</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math></meaning>
</definition>
</glossary>
